      <div class="info-card"><div class="info-card-ico"><Icon name="heart" size={22} /></div><strong>Anxiety Reduction</strong><p>A 2009 RCT in the Journal of Clinical Psychopharmacology found chamomile extract significantly reduced GAD symptoms. A 2016 long-term study confirmed 38 weeks of daily use maintained anxiety reduction without diminishing effectiveness.</p></div>
      <div class="info-card"><div class="info-card-ico"><Icon name="leaf" size={22} /></div><strong>Digestive Calm</strong><p>Bisabolol and chamazulene relax smooth muscle in the gastrointestinal tract, reducing bloating, cramping, and nervous stomach. This makes chamomile uniquely effective for stress that manifests as digestive discomfort.</p></div>
      <div class="info-card"><div class="info-card-ico"><Icon name="moon" size={22} /></div><strong>Gentle Sleep Support</strong><p>While not a potent sedative, chamomile's calming effects facilitate the mental transition from wakefulness to sleep. Best for people whose insomnia stems from racing thoughts and anxiety rather than circadian disruption.</p></div>
    </div>

    <div class="callout">
      <p>A randomized controlled trial published in <em>Phytomedicine</em> (2016) found that <strong>long-term chamomile supplementation (1,500mg/day for 38 weeks) significantly reduced anxiety relapse rates</strong> in patients with moderate-to-severe generalized anxiety disorder, while simultaneously improving overall well-being scores. Importantly, no tolerance, dependency, or withdrawal effects were observed during the 38-week study period.</p>
      <cite>Mao et al. — Phytomedicine (2016)</cite>
    </div>

